{"word":"τιμητέος","slug":"τιμητέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τιμητέος</b></el> <el>(τιμητέος, η, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:τιμάω'><el>τιμάω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be honoured, valued</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>τιμητέον</el>, <i>one must honour, esteem, estimate</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}